# Supabase Configuration
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 
# These environment variables are required for Supabase authentication and 
# cloud data sync in RecordQuest.
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com and create a project
# 2. In your Supabase dashboard, go to Settings → API
# 3. Copy your Project URL and anon public key
# 4. Create a .env file in the project root (same folder as package.json)
# 5. Add these variables with your actual values (see examples below)
# 6. Run: npx expo start
# 7. The app will read these values automatically (Expo prefix EXPO_PUBLIC_*)
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Never commit .env to git (it contains secrets)
# - Add ".env" to .gitignore
# - Env variables with EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix are safe to use in React Native apps
# - The anon key is public and cannot access other users' data (Row Level Security)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Your Supabase project URL
# Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your-project-url-here

# Your Supabase anonymous public API key
# Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Google Maps / Places API key (used by Store Finder Google Places API New)
# Example: AIzaSyDxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here
